data.content:
## What breaks: Cosmos DB sync I/O is **fully removed** in EF Core 11

In .NET 10, you opted into sync-over-async for the Cosmos provider. In .NET 11, **that opt-in no longer exists** — all synchronous I/O calls **always throw**, with no workaround.

Every method in your repository is affected:

```csharp
public class ProductRepository
{
    private readonly CosmosDbContext _context;

    public async Task<List<Product>> GetAllAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.ToListAsync();       // was ToList()
    }

    public async Task<Product> GetByIdAsync(int id)
    {
        return await _context.Products.FirstAsync(p => p.Id == id); // was First()
    }

    public async Task<int> GetCountAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.CountAsync();        // was Count()
    }

    public async Task SaveAsync(Product product)
    {
        _context.Products.Add(product);
        await _context.SaveChangesAsync();                  // was SaveChanges()
    }
}
```

**The mapping:**
| .NET 10 (sync) | .NET 11 (async required) |
|---|---|
| `ToList()` | `await ToListAsync()` |
| `First()` | `await FirstAsync()` |
| `Count()` | `await CountAsync()` |
| `SaveChanges()` | `await SaveChangesAsync()` |

This will ripple up — every caller of these methods must also become `async`. There is no configuration flag to restore the old behavior.
